                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="12757627" author="noble.paul" created="Sat, 19 Sep 2009 05:53:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 . &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12757640" author="noble.paul" created="Sat, 19 Sep 2009 09:28:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is not the complete patch . only code changes .I guess we should change it in 1.4 itself&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757641" author="noble.paul" created="Sat, 19 Sep 2009 10:03:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Let us see if we can clean this up in this release itself ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757647" author="noble.paul" created="Sat, 19 Sep 2009 11:07:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This would mean that the configuration of mergePolicy and mergeScheduler become as follows&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;mergePolicy class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.LogByteSizeMergePolicy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;mergeSceduler class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.ConcurrentMergeScheduler&quot;&lt;/span&gt; /&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;any setters of the class can be invoked on these classes by keeping attributes&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757793" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 04:17:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Noble, looks good, can you include a test case?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757798" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 04:33:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually if we&apos;re going to change the solrconfig xml schema, I think it should look like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;mergePolicy class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.LogByteSizeMergePolicy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;maxMergeMB&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;64.0&amp;lt;/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/mergePolicy&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;mergeSceduler class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.ConcurrentMergeScheduler&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;maxThreadCount&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;3&amp;lt;/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/mergeScheduler&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attributes are limiting.  This way we can add more complex objects in the future if needed.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757808" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 05:11:10 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;attributes are limiting. This way we can add more complex objects in the future if needed. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are not limiting to attributes. If the Object is a NamedListInitializedPlugin it can use the sub attributes also. If we use external classes we cannot dictate that class to  implement a NamedListInitializedPlugin . So let us have both &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757817" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 05:46:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch with a test case that implements init args.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we stick with one system, it&apos;s less to document and debug later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757827" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 07:08:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Jason .I am fine with this.  I plan to commit this shortly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757830" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 07:47:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;all the conf files needed to be modified for this&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12757870" author="noble.paul" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 12:30:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;a test was failing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758050" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Mon, 21 Sep 2009 23:31:06 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Noble, looks good, and all tests pass.  I think it&apos;s tricky to commit this as is, because there&apos;s no back compat?  Maybe we can allow:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;mergePolicy&amp;gt;org.apache.lucene.index.LogByteSizeMergePolicy&amp;lt;/mergePolicy&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;mergeScheduler&amp;gt;org.apache.lucene.index.ConcurrentMergeScheduler&amp;lt;/mergeScheduler&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;mergePolicy14 class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.LogByteSizeMergePolicy&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;maxMergeMB&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;64.0&amp;lt;/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/mergePolicy14&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;mergeSceduler14 class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;org.apache.lucene.index.ConcurrentMergeScheduler&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
  &amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;maxThreadCount&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;3&amp;lt;/&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;/mergeScheduler14&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s ugly but more clear and this way users&apos; installations won&apos;t immediately break on deployment.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12758111" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 04:50:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, there is no back-compat. but changing the tag-name is not an option&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ideal fix would be to support both syntaxes.I guess it is still possible.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="12758113" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 04:58:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Why is changing the tag name not an option?  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758118" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 05:22:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;the back-compat thing is a temporary thing. After we remove it we would love to keep the name as mergePolicy or mergeScheduler itself. There is no reason we should have this arbitrary number at the end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758235" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 14:06:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;supports both syntax. logs out a warning if the old syntax is used&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758240" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 14:14:54 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;committed : r817650&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks Jason&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758244" author="noble.paul" created="Tue, 22 Sep 2009 14:24:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;this turned out to be a lot bigger&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758588" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 06:21:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we need a legacy test?  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758591" author="jasonrutherglen" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 06:45:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a legacy test, and fixed a small NPE bug that happens via SolrPlugUtils&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12758608" author="noble.paul" created="Wed, 23 Sep 2009 07:31:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;committed r817976&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks Jason&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760090" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 27 Sep 2009 20:46:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-opening because the mergeScheduler and mergePolicy specified in the indexDefaults section is not honored.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760091" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 27 Sep 2009 21:04:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a test case which fails.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Still trying to understand and debug.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760095" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 27 Sep 2009 21:33:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix which passes the test case posted earlier. I&apos;ll commit this shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12760098" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 27 Sep 2009 21:42:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 819401.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775883" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:52:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
